 @Shadow Blade  this is just a pet peeve of mine but I advise you to not capitalize the first letter of every word you write, it should be used for names only (cities, countries and people).

Now, is quite literally impossible for anyone who's not asian to learn something like japanese in a week, nevermind the writing, even speaking would be impossible; there are at the very least 2000 different words in a complex language such as japanese and there are maybe 2 to 3 meanings for certain words that might sound alike or the same (just being totally different while written), to learn such amount of words any normal person would need at the very least 1 month and that's just to learn them, you'd need to get used to it and know the nuances to be able to actually use them in a speech so that would be another month.

Learning japanese in 1 week is impossible for someone normal, if you know of an example fine, that's extremely rare and incredible but too high of a standard, the usual is 2 months to be able to communicate in another language, just enough to be understood and understand I must add.

